<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="407" type="conservation">
<paragraph blockId="14.[1396,2601,2224,2888]" pageId="14" pageNumber="407">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1398,1754,2736,2769]" pageId="14" pageNumber="407">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Not assessed on The IUCN Red List. McCarthy's Shrew was only recently described based on a specimen collected in 1995. Additional studies are needed to assess its threats, but it is found in Celaque National Park.
</paragraph>
